metadata.name: Nanven.
metadata.description:
Standing on a slippery rock during this long exposure was not for the faint hearted. Every few seconds a fresh wave would come crashing in around these boulders, many of them washing over the rock I was stood on, soaking my feet in the process. Despite the serene appearance of the image it was wild to say the least !. The things we do for a photograph.
Porth Nanven, Cornwall, UK.
